# Testing Requirements

## Engine Tests (Vitest)

- Every engine module must have corresponding tests
- Use deterministic seeds: `createLCG(42)` for reproducible tests
- Coverage thresholds: 80% lines, 80% functions, 70% branches
- Golden tests: specific seed → specific expected output

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
import { createLCG } from '../../src/sim/RNG.js';

describe('moduleName', () => {
  it('produces deterministic output', () => {
    const rng = createLCG(42);
    const result = myFunction(rng, input);
    expect(result).toEqual(expectedOutput);
  });
});
```

## What to Test

- Core logic correctness (cap calculations, progression curves, trade values)
- Event bus integration (module A emits → module B reacts correctly)
- Edge cases (empty roster, max cap, rookie with 0 experience)
- Invariants (cap never negative, roster never > 53, all IDs unique)

## What NOT to Test

- UI rendering (save for Playwright E2E)
- Third-party library internals
- Simple type re-exports
